<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[144,1029,1310,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
One specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OLIVIER" authorityYear="1807" box="[351,482,1348,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Brachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis box="[351,482,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">B. cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found feeding on the endemic 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Galanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elwesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Galanthus elwesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the Oros Ambelos (
<figureCitation box="[485,550,1385,1409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[144,173,792,810]" captionTargetBox="[144,1028,113,768]" captionTargetId="figure-162@5.[144,1028,113,771]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Brachycerus cinereus OLIVIER, 1807 in the Oros Ambelos feeding on leaves of Galanthus elwesii. Photo: C. Germann." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5851458/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), a genus which was not yet documented as a feeding plant for any 
<taxonomicName box="[434,573,1422,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Brachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[434,573,1422,1446]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[144,1029,1310,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
More than 40 species of 
<taxonomicName box="[459,595,1460,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Brachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,595,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from the Palaearctic realm, most of them in the Mediterranean region (Friedman &amp; Sagiv 2010). The host plants and feeding plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[464,597,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Brachycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,597,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brachycerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are 
<taxonomicName box="[649,820,1534,1558]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaryllidaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[831,923,1534,1558]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Araceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[933,1028,1534,1558]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Liliaceae</taxonomicName>
and interestingly also 
<taxonomicName box="[378,512,1572,1596]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Orchidaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Germann, Ch." box="[522,684,1572,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="233 - 238" refId="ref5920" refString="Germann, Ch. (2003): Erfolgreiche Zucht von Brachycerus undatus (Fabricius, 1798), (Coleoptera: Curculionidae, Brachycerinae). - Snudebiller 4: 233 - 238." type="journal article" year="2003">Germann 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Germann, Ch." box="[696,751,1572,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref5955" refString="Germann, Ch. (2009): Bericht uber eine Exkursion nach Kreta (Griechenland) mit Einblicken in die Russelkafer-Fauna (Coleoptera, Curculionoidea). - Weevil News 46: 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
, Friedman &amp; Sagiv 2010).
</paragraph>
